# VYLUX Railway Deployment - Self-Hosted Supabase
# Architecture: Railway PostgreSQL + PostgREST + App

# ===========================================
# STEP 1: Railway PostgreSQL Plugin
# ===========================================
# In Railway dashboard: "+ New" → "Database" → "PostgreSQL"
# Railway auto-injects DATABASE_URL. Note the internal hostname.

# ===========================================
# STEP 2: PostgREST Service (set on this Railway service)
# ===========================================
# Create new service: Docker Hub → postgrest/postgrest
# Set these env vars on the PostgREST service:
PGRST_DB_URI=postgresql://postgres:PASSWORD@postgres.railway.internal:5432/railway
PGRST_DB_SCHEMAS=public
PGRST_DB_ANON_ROLE=anon
PGRST_JWT_SECRET=i51VeqhMHU0mzVLUAOdG4gRTAXWUngj8
PGRST_DB_MAX_ROWS=1000
PGRST_SERVER_PORT=3000

# ===========================================
# STEP 3: App Service (set on this Railway service)
# ===========================================
# Uses Dockerfile.railway. Set these env vars:
SUPABASE_URL=http://postgrest.railway.internal:3000
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJyb2xlIjoic2VydmljZV9yb2xlIiwiaXNzIjoic3VwYWJhc2UiLCJpYXQiOjE3ODMyMzQxMTQsImV4cCI6MjA5ODU5NDExNH0.cg2peqpVpz59szMmJJpZEBcz-DuWmfWNmsw0BWmrhfs
NODE_ENV=production

# ===========================================
# STEP 4: Initialize Database
# ===========================================
# Connect to Railway PostgreSQL and run:
# 1. packages/database/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql
# 2. packages/database/seeds/01_design_tokens.sql
# 3. supabase/rls_policies.sql (AFTER Supabase image init)

# ===========================================
# STEP 5: Generate New JWT Keys (optional)
# ===========================================
# Run: node scripts/generate-jwt.js
# Update PGRST_JWT_SECRET and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY with new keys

# ===========================================
# LOBEHUB (AI features)
# ===========================================
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key
